// 2026-phase7-target-cleanup.vox — Migration M-70.
//
// SCAFFOLD ONLY. This file exists to reserve the path and document the
// intended shape. The actual implementation lands in migration item M-70
// (see docs/src/architecture/data-storage-migration-backlog-2026.md).
//
// Run: vox run scripts/migrations/2026-phase7-target-cleanup.vox
// Dry:  vox run scripts/migrations/2026-phase7-target-cleanup.vox --check
//
// Purpose
// -------
// Remove abandoned `target-*` directories left over from ad-hoc per-profile
// cargo invocations (target-clippy, target-codex, target-coverage, target-doc,
// target-nextest, target-test, target-bench) and add `target-*/` to
// `.gitignore` so they cannot return under any tracked-path pattern.
//
// Idempotency
// -----------
// A second run is a no-op: the directories are already gone, and the
// `.gitignore` append block is marked with a comment pair that the script
// detects before inserting.
//
// Exit codes
// ----------
// 0 — all target-* dirs absent or successfully removed; .gitignore updated.
// 1 — in --check mode, divergence detected (still-present dirs or missing
//     gitignore stanza).
// 2 — I/O error or refusal (e.g., .gitignore contains BOM — see M-74).
//
// vox:skip  — body is illustrative; actual implementation in M-70.

fn main() {
    // TODO(M-70):
