    //   4. Otherwise, rm -rf the directory (respecting --check).
    //   5. Read `.gitignore`, and if the sentinel block
    //        # >>> M-70 target-* cleanup >>>
    //        target-*/
    //        # <<< M-70 target-* cleanup <<<
    //      is absent, append it.
    //   6. Refuse to operate if the first three bytes of `.gitignore` are
    //      0xEF 0xBB 0xBF (UTF-8 BOM) — the M-74 guard must run first.

    // See also: the data-storage-guard sub-check `abandoned-target-dir`.
